# Borki, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Borki () is a rural locality (a settlement) in Kabansky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 184 as of 2010. There are 2 streets.
Geography
Borki is located  northwest of Kabansk (the district's administrative centre) by road. Tvorogovo is the nearest rural locality.
